
[1]arnoldist

   'ARNOLDIST, n. A disciple of Arnold of Brescia, who in the 12th
   century, preached against the Romish Church, for which he was banished;
   but he was afterwards permitted to return. By his preaching, an
   insurrection was excited, for which he was condemned and executed.
